---
import "../../styles/global.css";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <title>JD Navigation - Xi Lin</title>
  </head>
  <body class="bg-white text-gray-900">
    <main class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-16 sm:px-10">
      <a href="/" class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-500 hover:text-gray-900">Back to home</a>
      <p class="mt-6 text-sm font-mono text-blue-600">JD.com | Embodied Navigation Algorithm Intern</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">Embodied Navigation for Real-World Instruction Following</h1>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-4xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
        At JD.com, I worked on the construction of an embodied navigation algorithm system. The internship covered VLN solution evaluation and selection, end-to-end real-robot data collection and model finetuning, outdoor deployment validation, and zero-shot ObjectNav exploration for future embodied retail scenarios.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-10 overflow-hidden rounded-[28px] border border-gray-200 bg-black">
        <video controls playsinline class="w-full">
          <source src="/assets/projects/jd-vln-demo.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
        </video>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
        <section class="rounded-3xl border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-6">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Program Core</h2>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
            <li>Systematically evaluated mainstream VLN methods in real-world scenarios for navigation performance and stability, and finally implemented video-language navigation validation based on StreamVLN.</li>
            <li>Built a full pipeline covering real-world data collection, model training, finetuning, and deployment, enabling stable VLN execution on real robots in outdoor environments.</li>
            <li>Completed real-world VLN validation in open environments, with the technical route intended for later embodied tasks in JD Mall scenarios.</li>
            <li>Designed and implemented a VLM-based zero-shot ObjectNav solution for indoor settings, and explored a transferable deployment path from VLM and VLFM models to real robots.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-3xl border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-6">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Tech Stack</h2>
          <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            {["VLN", "ObjectNav", "Real Robot Data Collection", "Model Finetune", "Video-LLMs", "Outdoor Deployment"].map((item) => (
              <span class="rounded-full border border-gray-300 bg-white px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium text-gray-700">
                {item}
              </span>
            ))}
          </div>

          <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">Research Outputs from This Stage</h2>
          <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
            <p>MORN extends this experience toward long-horizon multi-goal ObjectNav with explicit resource-rational executive control.</p>
            <p>Dual-Anchoring extends this line toward VLN state-drift mitigation by anchoring both progress and history representations.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-5 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
            <a href="/publications/morn" class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-gray-900 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white hover:bg-gray-700">View MORN</a>
            <a href="/publications/dual-anchoring" class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 hover:border-gray-900 hover:text-gray-900">View Dual-Anchoring</a>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
